      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my tomato plants are looking kind of weird. the leaves at the bottom are turning yellow but the ones at the top look fine. do u know what might be happening and how i can fix the soil?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, it sounds like your tomato plants are experiencing a common issue known as \"lowered vigor,\" which can be caused by several factors, including poor soil drainage, nutrient imbalances, or even a root disease. To fix the soil, you should first ensure it has good drainage and is rich in organic matter. You can add compost or well-rotted manure to improve the soil structure. Also, consider testing your soil pH and nutrient levels to ensure they are within the optimal range for tomato plants, which is slightly acidic to neutral (pH 6.0-7.0). If the problem persists, you might want to check for root diseases or pests that could be affecting the lower leaves. Remember, healthy soil is key to happy plants, so take your time and give your tomato plants the best care they can receive.",
